data.description:
Nestled in the heart of Cooper City, this charming home, affectionately named ''Creeping Fig Cottage,'' is a true gem. With 3 bedrooms, 1 bathroom, and 1,174 square feet, this cozy abode offers comfort and style. Fully updated features include a 2017 roof, plumbing, and A/C system for peace of mind. Mohawk's TecWood flooring in European White Oak adds elegance, while its durability suits daily living. Enjoy convenient amenities like an LG washer/dryer, outdoor shed, chicken coop, and picnic area. With sought-after schools and amenities within walking distance, this home epitomizes Florida living. Experience the epitome of culinary delight in the spacious kitchen designed for the home chef. Adorned with a pot filler, handcrafted subway tile backsplash, and exquisite butcher block countertops, this kitchen exudes both style and functionality. Solid wood, American-made J&K cabinetry, complete with real brass knobs and bin pulls, adds a touch of elegance to the space.

Prepare delicious meals effortlessly with the LG Studio series stove, featuring a convenient proof setting perfect for homemade bread. Accommodate all your culinary needs with the extra-large LG stainless refrigerator, offering ample space for organization. Conceal your dishes in the large farm sink or breeze through clean-up with the ultra-quiet Maytag dishwasher.

Step into the cozy living areas adorned with shiplap, board and batten, crown molding, and large baseboards, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere. Retreat to the bath boasting timeless subway tile in the shower, classic Penny tile flooring, and a new mid-century modern vanity.

Embrace outdoor living in the tranquil outdoor spaces, featuring raised bed gardens, a spacious gazebo, and a covered porch with an outdoor shower area. Perfect for backyard farm enthusiasts, the property also includes a large chicken run.

Experience peace of mind knowing that the entire house has been re-plumbed, eliminating cast iron pipes commonly found in typical homes in the area.

Conveniently located within walking distance are Cooper City's highly-rated Elementary, Middle, and High schools, allowing you to skip the lines and enjoy a leisurely walk with your children to school.
